    <text>
        <body>
        	<div1 type="letter">
        		<head>Jim to Mademoiselle Marcelle Guerin <date value="1916-09-17">Sept 17th 1916</date></head>
        		
        		<opener>
            <dateline><date value="1916-09-17">Sept 17th 1916</date></dateline>
            
            <salute>Dear Marcelle:</salute>
        		</opener>
        		
            <p>
            Yes, I am much
            better and am arguing
            with the Major now to
            let me go.  I am afraid
            tho [sic] that I shall be kept
            here for another week.  They
            have a new stunt now of
            putting hot pads on me.
            The name sounds like Cat a place.
            When I get up after writing
            
            <pb n="[p.2]"/>
            
            a letter or after sitting
            for any length of time
            in a chair is when it
            hurts most.  However it
            isn’t bad enough now to
            keep me from doing my 
            job.
            </p><p>
            I’m anxious to see 
            the lion cub.  When he
            gets big enough we can
            just drop him over 
            with the Boches.
            
            <pb n="[p.3]"/>
            
            My fair Yvonne is taking
            her vacation now.  Don’t
            I have hard luck though?
            </p><p>
            Hurrah we all got <unclear>chan [sp?]</unclear>
            night gowns last night.
            The sister announced “Pour
            les anciens sentement”  That’s
            good isn’t it?  You 
            have to be an old land
            mark here before you
            draw one.
            
            <pb n="[p.4]"/>
            
            Well Marcelle, hope you
            don’t have to keep up
            working so hard &mdash; can’t 
            you take it easy?
            </p>
        		
        		<closer>
            <signed>Jim</signed>
            
            <seg type="postscript">
            Hopital Mixte<lb/>
            Vitry le Francois.<lb/>
            Marne.
            </seg>
        		</closer>
        		
            <!-- [With this letter is an envelope addressed to Mademoiselle Marcelle Guerin, 148 Bis Rue de Longchamp, XVI e, Paris.] -->
            
            </div1>
        </body>
